-A (Append):
Appends a rule to the end of the specified chain.

-D (Delete):
Deletes a rule from the specified chain based on its specification.

-I (Insert):
Inserts a rule at the specified position in the chain.

-L (List):
Lists the rules in the specified chain.

-F (Flush):
Flushes all rules from the specified chain.

-P (Policy):
Sets the policy for the specified chain.

-s (Source):
Specifies the source IP address or network.

-d (Destination):
Specifies the destination IP address or network.

-p (Protocol):
Specifies the protocol of the rule (e.g., tcp, udp, icmp).

--dport (Destination Port):
Specifies the destination port.

--sport (Source Port):
Specifies the source port.

-j (Jump):
Specifies the target of the rule (e.g., ACCEPT, DROP, REJECT).

-m (Match):
Specifies an extended match module.

-i (Input Interface):
Specifies the input interface.

-o (Output Interface):
Specifies the output interface.

-c (Packet and Byte Counters):
Resets packet and byte counters for a rule.

--line-numbers:
Shows line numbers in the iptables -L output.

-v (Verbose):
Provides more detailed output.

-n (Numeric):
Displays numeric values instead of resolving IP addresses and port numbers.
